## Layout System

All section pages (`/`, `/work`, `/studio`, `/blog`, `/timeline`) are wrapped in `SiteLayout`, which renders:

```
#shell
  header.topbar          ‚Üê sticky header via SiteHeader
  .dial                  ‚Üê fixed-position mode dial
  main.stage
    .mode#mode-*         ‚Üê one per route, overflow-y: auto (the scroll container)
  <CaseStudy />          ‚Üê slide-in overlay
  <VideoModal />         ‚Üê portal modal for YouTube iframes
```

`body { overflow: hidden }` ‚Äî all scrolling happens inside `.mode` containers.

**Blog post pages** (`/blog/*`) bypass `SiteLayout` entirely (detected in `_app.js` by `router.pathname.startsWith('/blog/')`). `BlogPost` renders its own layout using `SiteHeader` + a full-scroll `body.post` class that overrides `overflow: hidden`.

---

## Context

`SiteContext` (exported from `SiteLayout.js`) provides three functions to any child component:

| Function | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `navigateTo(modeId)` | View Transition-aware navigation to a mode |
| `openCase(key)` | Opens the CaseStudy overlay for a key from `CASE_DATA` |
| `openVideo(youtubeId)` | Opens VideoModal with an autoplaying YouTube iframe |

Usage: `const { navigateTo, openCase, openVideo } = useContext(SiteContext)`

---

## Blog System

- Each post lives at `pages/blog/<slug>/index.mdx`
- Every MDX file defines a `meta` object and wraps content in `<BlogPost meta={meta}>`
- `getAllPosts.js` uses Node.js `fs` to scan `pages/blog/*/index.mdx`, parses `meta` via regex, and returns posts sorted newest-first
- `getStaticProps` in `pages/blog.js` and `pages/index.js` call `getAllPosts()` at build time
- Template for new posts: `pages/blog/_template.mdx`

### Meta shape
```js
export const meta = {
  title: 'Post Title',
  date: 'YYYY-MM-DD',
  description: 'One sentence description.',
  image: '/path/to/cover.jpg',  // optional ‚Äî shown as card thumbnail
  readTime: 5,                  // minutes
  tags: ['tag1', 'tag2'],
}
```

